Yes they all have the hatch (egg crate) we were very aware of the
differences. The 1960's era (early) was copied from an NOS mat that I have
(going to Robert Davis) that came with my late 59 single cab I once owned.
It isn't even cut to go around the steering column, actually there are no
slits in it, but does have the OG VW partnumber and markings.

ronnie

I will let people with late model buses deal with the high beam switch hole
and the bigger hole for the e-brake boot (what's that?)

