er- Ronnie, there were three different shape floor mats used from ch 501 xxx

(forward shifter) through 67,

the earlier kind has a slit for the ebrake handle, which used a metal cover 
for the ebrake cable ends, not the rubber ugly boot thing

then they went to the oval hole, when they introduced the ugly rubber boot 
(1962 model year?)

then they stuck the high beam on the turn sig switch, rather than the floor.

but it is great you are getting nice repros.  These have the hatch pattern 
underneath?
